</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bombs exploded near a troop truck in Yugoslavia's riot-torn Kosovo province and 
outside a Serbian newspaper office in Croatia, causing no injuries but sparking 
fears that ethnic Albanians may be resorting to guerrilla attacks in their 
fight against Serbian dominance, officials said. The blasts followed riots by 
Albanians in Kosovo last week that left 24 people dead. The riots erupted after 
officials in Serbia, the largest of Yugoslavia's six republics, imposed curbs 
on the southern province's autonomy to permit a crackdown on nationalists who 
are accused of persecuting local Serbs. 
</P>
