<P>
3 NEW SITES FOR SUPERFUND LIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three San Joaquin Valley sites have been added to the Environmental Protection 
Agency's Superfund list of the nation's most polluted areas. The expanded list 
was released in Washington and among 101 new entries were an old Southern 
California Edison pole dipping yard in Visalia and areas in Modesto and Turlock 
where soil and ground water are contaminated. Superfund status potentially 
makes available special funding to clean up the polluted sites which are 
considered the greatest long-term threat to humans and the environment. 
</P>
