<P>
MISSING WOMAN, 77, FOUND IN SUNLAND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 77-year-old woman missing from a senior citizen day-care center in Sunland 
since last Tuesday has been found, police said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Lenore Jones, who suffers from memory loss, was found Saturday about 1:30 p.m. 
near Oro Vista Avenue and McGroarty Place in Sunland by two youths who were 
hiking, Los Angeles police Sgt. Ken Dionne said. The location is about 
three-fourths of a mile from the Canyon Senior Adult Day Care Center, from 
where Jones was reported missing. 
</P>
