<TEXT>
<P>
Ella Fitzgerald, who will celebrate her 71st birthday April 25, will be honored 
April 28 in a gala tribute at the Beverly Hilton Hotel. Bill Cosby will host 
the event, which will raise funds for the Society of Singers, an organization 
launched in 1984 to offer financial and other assistance to singers in need. 
Among the performers set to participate are Mel Torme, Joe Williams, Dionne 
Warwick, George Shearing, the Pointer Sisters, Manhattan Transfer, Patti 
Austin, Carol Burnett, the Frank Capp/Nat Pierce Juggernaut big band, and an 
all-star jazz group led by the saxophonist Benny Carter, who discovered 
Fitzgerald when she was 15. During the evening the first of a series of annual 
trophies honoring lifetime achievements, to be known as "The Ellas," will be 
awarded. The first recipient will be Ella Fitzgerald herself; the award is 
tentatively set to be presented by Clint Eastwood. ALEENE MacMINN and Claudia 
Puig 
