<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITISH QUEEN WORTH KING'S RANSOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Old money still dominates Britain, according to a survey published Sunday that 
shows Queen Elizabeth is still by far the richest person in the country with 
assets of $8.9 billion. 
</P>
<P>
Although the number of millionaires has risen from 5,000 to 20,000 in the last 
five years, the study of the richest 200 people in Britain showed more than 
half inherited their wealth, the Sunday Times said. Only 86 of the 200 made 
their fortunes themselves. 
</P>
