<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINESE WOMEN REACH TABLE TENNIS FINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By AP 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DORTMUND, West Germany 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China's women reached their ninth straight team final at the World Table Tennis 
Championships. 
</P>
<P>
Led by Olympic champion Chen Jing and Li Huifen, the Chinese beat Sweden and 
Hong Kong by 3-0 scores on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
In men's play, Sweden and North Korea won their quarterfinal matches. Sweden 
defeated West Germany 5-2, while North Korea downed Japan 5-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
