<TEXT>
<P>
Former Texas A&amp;M football player George Smith reversed his field again, 
denying a published report that he was offered $30,000 to recant charges he was 
paid "hush money" for his silence about National Collegiate Athletic Assn. 
rules violations at the university, the Bryan (Tex.) Eagle reported. 
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that in a Saturday night telephone interview from his home 
in Atlanta, Smith denied a report in Saturday's editions of the Dallas Morning 
News in which he was quoted as saying he was offered about $30,000 by a 
university official to recant earlier charges that former A&amp;M coach Jackie 
Sherrill broke NCAA rules. 
</P>
