<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
HONORARY LEGISLATORS WILL REPRESENT ELDERLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange County Community Services Agency has announced the names of seven 
recently elected honorary Senior Legislators who will represent the interests 
of the county's elderly population. 
</P>
<P>
More than 20 candidates ran for the seats, with the election conducted by the 
Area Agency on Aging and the Senior Citizens Advisory Council. 
</P>
<P>
Elected as Senior Senators were Neel Buell of Costa Mesa and Will Armstrong of 
Buena Park. 
</P>
<P>
Lobbying the Assembly will be Marcella Surowic of Santa Ana, George Brown of 
Seal Beach, John Kumbera of Brea, Muriel Nelson of Anaheim and Helen Mills of 
Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
The representatives will visit area legislators in Sacramento in October and 
lobby causes important to the county's aged population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
